1
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:21,460
[2000]

2
00:00:36,900 --> 00:00:39,530
[Electromechanical Workshop
| Zhu Jialong | Welder]

3
00:01:03,520 --> 00:01:05,280
Even a dog costs more than this.

4
00:01:05,640 --> 00:01:06,560
What's wrong with you?

5
00:01:06,560 --> 00:01:08,160
Do you treat us like animals?

6
00:01:13,360 --> 00:01:14,950
Yes, I'm treating you like animals.

7
00:01:14,950 --> 00:01:16,200
So what?

8
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:51,900
[THE GUILTY]

9
00:02:52,150 --> 00:02:57,810
[Episode 7]

10
00:02:57,890 --> 00:03:00,370
[Welcome Foreign Guests
to Nanping Shipyard]

11
00:03:00,370 --> 00:03:01,370
Mr. Ma,

12
00:03:02,070 --> 00:03:04,950
you promised the
delivery of the product

13
00:03:05,910 --> 00:03:08,470
for the fourth quarter of last year.

14
00:03:10,280 --> 00:03:12,190
It's been delayed a month.

15
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:13,660
Mr. Ma,

16
00:03:14,030 --> 00:03:16,200
You swore to us solemnly

17
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:17,800
that you would deliver the product

18
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:19,630
in the fourth quarter of last year.

19
00:03:19,630 --> 00:03:20,910
Yet we've already granted you
a three-month

20
00:03:20,910 --> 00:03:22,310
extension for delivery.

21
00:03:22,470 --> 00:03:24,120
Now, the second quarter is almost over,

22
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:25,300
and it's still not delivered.

23
00:03:25,300 --> 00:03:26,370
Mr. Thomas,

24
00:03:26,910 --> 00:03:29,300
there was an unforeseen accident
at the shipyard.

25
00:03:29,300 --> 00:03:32,180
Mr. Ma's family also encountered
some... difficulties.

26
00:03:32,180 --> 00:03:33,910
We ask for your understanding.

27
00:03:39,910 --> 00:03:43,190
I regret what happened
to your company and your family.

28
00:03:43,220 --> 00:03:45,520
I regret what happened
to your company and your family.

29
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:47,579
But business is business.

30
00:03:47,620 --> 00:03:50,090
We demand to terminate our cooperation
with your company

31
00:03:50,090 --> 00:03:52,350
and claim corresponding compensation.

32
00:03:57,710 --> 00:03:58,630
Tell him.

33
00:04:01,040 --> 00:04:02,880
Terminating the contract is fine.

34
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:04,500
Compensation is no problem either.

35
00:04:04,500 --> 00:04:05,770
But I guarantee you this:

36
00:04:05,770 --> 00:04:08,030
starting today, not a single shipyard
in the entire Lingnan region

37
00:04:08,030 --> 00:04:11,150
will accept your orders.

38
00:04:22,520 --> 00:04:23,760
Mr. Ma.

39
00:04:24,220 --> 00:04:26,430
When the lion king gets older,

40
00:04:27,960 --> 00:04:31,960
the new lion will drive him
away from the tribe.

41
00:04:32,630 --> 00:04:37,950
And then the old lion will wander alone
in the jungle for the rest of his life,

42
00:04:38,620 --> 00:04:43,860
until maybe one day,
a wise dog bites him to his death.

43
00:04:48,810 --> 00:04:51,320
Mr. Ma, you are getting older.

44
00:04:51,580 --> 00:04:53,020
Lingnan Shipyards

45
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:55,159
are not under your control.

46
00:04:55,630 --> 00:04:59,180
I advise you not to feel so confident.

47
00:04:59,570 --> 00:05:01,580
[Welcome Foreign Guests
to Nanping Shipyard]

48
00:05:06,070 --> 00:05:11,480
[Welcome Foreign Guests
to Nanping Shipyard]

49
00:05:11,630 --> 00:05:12,310
Find out

50
00:05:13,070 --> 00:05:14,800
which shipyard took his order.

51
00:05:15,110 --> 00:05:16,240
Understood, Mr. Ma.

52
00:05:19,070 --> 00:05:20,670
I quit my job at the shipyard.

53
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:22,090
Are you nuts?

54
00:05:22,650 --> 00:05:24,550
Have you lost your senses?

55
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:27,040
Don't you know you're a cripple?

56
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:28,170
What else can you do?

57
00:05:28,230 --> 00:05:30,170
If I hadn't sent cigarettes
to the workshop foreman back then,

58
00:05:30,170 --> 00:05:31,760
could you have gotten into the shipyard?

59
00:05:31,760 --> 00:05:33,000
Just up and quit without a word!

60
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:34,120
Who did you tell?

61
00:05:34,159 --> 00:05:35,270
Did you tell anyone at all?

62
00:05:35,270 --> 00:05:36,680
Enough, enough, enough!

63
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:37,740
What are you doing?

64
00:05:37,750 --> 00:05:38,560
The kid's grown up。

65
00:05:38,560 --> 00:05:39,890
Spare him some dignity.

66
00:05:39,890 --> 00:05:41,480
You raised this good-for-nothing!

67
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:42,560
I'll even hit you.

68
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:44,480
I'll hit... I'll hit you, too.

69
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:47,040
Try hitting my mom one more time!

70
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:48,920
Son! Son! Son!

71
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:49,720
Just try it!

72
00:05:50,159 --> 00:05:52,920
Let go, Son! Son! Son!

73
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:55,320
Let go! Let go!

74
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:57,870
Son, let go!

75
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:04,870
Lin Wenge,

76
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:06,610
I'm telling you,

77
00:06:06,940 --> 00:06:08,600
if you dare touch my mom again,

78
00:06:08,830 --> 00:06:10,000
I'll kill you!

79
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:13,750
Son.

80
00:06:18,100 --> 00:06:19,300
Someone's here.

81
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:20,520
Open the door.

82
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:26,810
Who are you looking for?

83
00:06:26,870 --> 00:06:28,400
What's all the noise about?

84
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:30,560
Lin Hua,

85
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:32,980
Mr. Ma asked me to say hello to you.

86
00:06:34,510 --> 00:06:35,690
M-Mr. Ma?

87
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:37,650
How did you find this place?

88
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:40,120
The house was left by the factory, right?

89
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:42,870
Now that you're laid off,

90
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:46,300
and Lin Hua doesn't work
at the factory anymore.

91
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:48,760
do you really think
you can still live here?

92
00:06:49,270 --> 00:06:50,240
That's a bit harsh, isn't it?

93
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:51,120
If we don't live here,

94
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:52,790
are we supposed to live on the streets?

95
00:06:52,790 --> 00:06:54,000
Your factory is so huge,

96
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:56,130
why bother with our poor little place?

97
00:06:56,159 --> 00:06:57,560
If Lin Hua got into trouble out there,

98
00:06:57,560 --> 00:06:58,750
you can scold him or hit him.

99
00:06:58,750 --> 00:07:00,480
Just... just don't kick us out.

100
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:04,240
Go get some tea.

101
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:05,240
Okay.

102
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:05,870
Mom.

103
00:07:07,390 --> 00:07:08,850
You two go outside for now.

104
00:07:11,550 --> 00:07:12,750
You brat.

105
00:07:12,830 --> 00:07:15,120
Let's go. Let him handle it himself.

106
00:07:25,830 --> 00:07:26,800
What do you want?

107
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:28,120
Sit down.

108
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,560
Mr. Ma didn't fire you,

109
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:35,190
yet you quit first.

110
00:07:35,830 --> 00:07:37,270
Found a better job?

111
00:07:38,430 --> 00:07:40,680
Or have you decided where you should go?

112
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:44,170
Where I go is none of your business.

113
00:07:46,120 --> 00:07:48,120
Lu's son is back.

114
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:50,520
Not sure what trouble he's caused outside.

115
00:07:51,610 --> 00:07:52,720
Keep it down.

116
00:07:57,909 --> 00:07:58,760
[Everlasting Bloom Florist]

117
00:07:58,790 --> 00:07:58,980
[Pay Up]

118
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:07,000
How did you find here?

119
00:08:08,390 --> 00:08:09,590
You're finally back.

120
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:14,530
I've had such a hard time finding you!

121
00:08:17,050 --> 00:08:17,120
[Pay Up]

122
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:19,600
Where have you been hiding
for the past 6 months?

123
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:21,560
Even a college student
didn't keep his word?

124
00:08:21,560 --> 00:08:23,080
Look, you are a grown man,

125
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:27,490
why are you still
making your family worry about you?

126
00:08:30,630 --> 00:08:31,360
By the way,

127
00:08:31,640 --> 00:08:34,100
I forgot the gifts I prepared
for your parents.

128
00:08:34,100 --> 00:08:35,950
I'll bring them over tomorrow.

129
00:08:35,970 --> 00:08:37,169
You're not a good son.

130
00:08:37,730 --> 00:08:39,320
I'll be one for you.

131
00:08:40,030 --> 00:08:40,630
We're off.

132
00:08:40,630 --> 00:08:42,030
[Pay Up]

133
00:08:42,030 --> 00:08:44,320
Think it through before you come to us.

134
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:45,430
Break it up.

135
00:08:46,030 --> 00:08:46,870
Break it up.

136
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:49,120
Lu Ming,

137
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:51,000
tell me.

138
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:54,250
What kind of trouble
have you really gotten into?

139
00:08:59,070 --> 00:09:00,160
How much do you owe?

140
00:09:02,280 --> 00:09:02,920
Dad.

141
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:07,240
Stay out of it.

142
00:09:21,230 --> 00:09:22,080
Lu Ming.

143
00:09:23,490 --> 00:09:25,510
You have to tell us what's going on.

144
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,260
You have to say tell us.

145
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:30,380
Say something!

146
00:09:30,380 --> 00:09:32,330
[Pay Up]

147
00:09:40,150 --> 00:09:41,000
Take this.

148
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:43,240
Pay the money back first.

149
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:44,770
Whether it's enough or not,

150
00:09:45,150 --> 00:09:47,740
we'll find a way to make up the rest.

151
00:09:48,670 --> 00:09:49,360
Dad.

152
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:52,670
This is my business.

153
00:09:53,510 --> 00:09:55,110
It has nothing to do with you.

154
00:09:56,210 --> 00:09:57,090
You bastard!

155
00:09:57,880 --> 00:09:59,810
What do you mean your own business?

156
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:01,810
The loan sharks are at our door.

157
00:10:02,470 --> 00:10:03,780
Do you expect me to watch

158
00:10:03,780 --> 00:10:05,440
you get killed on the street?

159
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:15,360
No matter what,

160
00:10:15,720 --> 00:10:17,390
get this settled today.

161
00:10:17,910 --> 00:10:18,750
Otherwise,

162
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:21,920
don't ever set foot in this house again!

163
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:34,390
[Lu Ming the Deadbeat: Dodges His Debts!]

164
00:10:42,770 --> 00:10:43,380
Lu Ming.

165
00:10:44,430 --> 00:10:47,330
Lu Ming! Lu Ming!

166
00:10:56,750 --> 00:10:57,630
Lin Hua.

167
00:10:58,600 --> 00:11:00,460
If you don't want to
work at the shipyard, fine.

168
00:11:00,460 --> 00:11:01,460
Mr. Ma won't care.

169
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:06,280
But you'd better stay put in Nanping
and behave yourself.

170
00:11:06,660 --> 00:11:07,660
If you leave,

171
00:11:08,400 --> 00:11:10,200
you must bear the consequences.

172
00:11:16,850 --> 00:11:17,650
Hi, Uncle Liu.

173
00:11:20,350 --> 00:11:21,550
The stairs are steep.

174
00:11:22,060 --> 00:11:23,350
Your legs aren't good,

175
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:24,260
Be careful.

176
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:53,080
This is all there is.

177
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:54,240
It's a bit rough.

178
00:11:59,320 --> 00:12:00,150
I'm leaving these things

179
00:12:00,150 --> 00:12:01,360
for you.

180
00:12:01,870 --> 00:12:03,270
The TV is broken.

181
00:12:03,270 --> 00:12:05,000
Keep it if you can fix it.

182
00:12:38,550 --> 00:12:39,640
Don't stop me.

183
00:12:39,660 --> 00:12:40,920
I want to see Uncle San.

184
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:43,260
Uncle San,

185
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:44,630
he's here.

186
00:12:44,840 --> 00:12:46,600
-Leave.
-Leave.

187
00:12:46,630 --> 00:12:47,870
Everyone out!

188
00:13:08,290 --> 00:13:09,950
How many times have I told you?

189
00:13:10,280 --> 00:13:11,920
Be polite to customers.

190
00:13:20,520 --> 00:13:21,570
College student,

191
00:13:23,740 --> 00:13:25,260
you finally show up.

192
00:13:27,620 --> 00:13:28,500
I'm sorry.

193
00:13:30,360 --> 00:13:31,390
I had something to take care of earlier.

194
00:13:31,390 --> 00:13:33,710
You're blaming me
for your personal business?

195
00:13:33,710 --> 00:13:35,550
Then go take care of it!

196
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:36,930
Pay back the money,

197
00:13:36,960 --> 00:13:38,120
and we're done.

198
00:13:38,670 --> 00:13:40,800
As long as you don't involve my family,

199
00:13:42,310 --> 00:13:43,640
I'm yours for anything,

200
00:13:44,050 --> 00:13:45,410
even my life.

201
00:13:48,050 --> 00:13:50,310
Do you have a misunderstanding about me?

202
00:13:52,360 --> 00:13:55,000
We do business with the living.

203
00:13:55,270 --> 00:13:56,240
My biggest fear

204
00:13:56,390 --> 00:13:58,120
is that my debtors die.

205
00:13:58,460 --> 00:14:00,310
So you have to stay alive

206
00:14:00,790 --> 00:14:02,550
and find a way to pay me back.

207
00:14:06,150 --> 00:14:07,680
Then let me tell you my plan.

208
00:14:08,180 --> 00:14:08,940
See that?

209
00:14:10,330 --> 00:14:12,300
This is what a college student is like!

210
00:14:12,300 --> 00:14:14,300
He comes up with a plan in an instant.

211
00:14:20,240 --> 00:14:21,480
I want to work for you.

212
00:14:25,020 --> 00:14:26,620
Are you crazy?

213
00:14:28,910 --> 00:14:31,270
See if they believe you.

214
00:14:39,720 --> 00:14:41,380
You really want to work for me?

215
00:14:42,230 --> 00:14:43,320
I did the math.

216
00:14:45,360 --> 00:14:47,080
I owe you 346,700.

217
00:14:47,740 --> 00:14:49,470
If I go out to work a regular job,

218
00:14:49,950 --> 00:14:51,810
I can't even pay off the interest.

219
00:14:51,950 --> 00:14:53,910
Interest—compound interest,

220
00:14:54,500 --> 00:14:55,830
it just keeps piling up.

221
00:14:57,840 --> 00:14:59,360
So I have to make quick money.

222
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:01,220
You want to make quick money here?

223
00:15:01,960 --> 00:15:02,870
How much do you think

224
00:15:02,870 --> 00:15:04,480
I should pay you a month?

225
00:15:05,370 --> 00:15:06,570
I don't want a salary.

226
00:15:07,270 --> 00:15:08,800
I just need the commission.

227
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:12,610
I'll collect debts for you.

228
00:15:13,030 --> 00:15:14,890
As long as I get enough money back,

229
00:15:15,030 --> 00:15:16,830
I'll definitely pay off my debt.

230
00:15:20,560 --> 00:15:23,560
A college student really
has a unique way of thinking!

231
00:15:24,300 --> 00:15:26,180
But talk is cheap.

232
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:27,640
Why should I believe you?

233
00:15:28,670 --> 00:15:30,470
Give me a debt you can't collect.

234
00:15:31,380 --> 00:15:32,780
I'll handle it right now.

235
00:15:39,650 --> 00:15:40,710
Chang, show me one.

236
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:49,730
The construction site on Xishui Road.

237
00:15:50,250 --> 00:15:51,950
Zhao Dabao, the construction foreman.

238
00:15:51,950 --> 00:15:55,200
[IOU: Zhao Dabao]

239
00:15:58,200 --> 00:15:59,730
What's my commission rate?

240
00:16:02,030 --> 00:16:02,830
I want 8%.

241
00:16:08,240 --> 00:16:10,600
You're crazy for money.

242
00:16:11,320 --> 00:16:13,120
You can't get this money anyway.

243
00:16:13,920 --> 00:16:15,160
8% isn't much.

244
00:16:20,120 --> 00:16:21,360
I agreed to

245
00:16:22,490 --> 00:16:23,490
an 8% commission.

246
00:16:24,110 --> 00:16:26,030
If you can get this million back,

247
00:16:26,050 --> 00:16:27,650
I can put your debt on hold,

248
00:16:27,680 --> 00:16:28,550
no interest accrued.

249
00:16:28,550 --> 00:16:30,000
And I promise you,

250
00:16:30,610 --> 00:16:32,540
no one will bother your parents

251
00:16:32,570 --> 00:16:33,600
or friends.

252
00:16:33,630 --> 00:16:35,000
What do you think?

253
00:16:46,720 --> 00:16:47,640
Uncle San.

254
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:52,270
Zhao Dabao is tough.

255
00:16:52,270 --> 00:16:54,240
He's backed by Ma Derong.

256
00:16:58,040 --> 00:17:00,040
The college boy is interesting.

257
00:17:22,510 --> 00:17:24,390
[Little Sun]

258
00:17:36,470 --> 00:17:40,370
[Little Sun]

259
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:41,980
[Little Sun: Play At Will]

260
00:17:52,440 --> 00:17:54,150
[Little Sun]

261
00:18:27,190 --> 00:18:28,810
It's not too late to back out.

262
00:19:19,260 --> 00:19:20,660
What are you doing there?

263
00:19:24,600 --> 00:19:25,880
Why aren't you working hard?

264
00:19:25,880 --> 00:19:27,100
What are you staring at?

265
00:19:27,100 --> 00:19:28,750
Did I hire you to inspect the place?

266
00:19:28,750 --> 00:19:30,070
You're just a lazy bum!

267
00:19:35,370 --> 00:19:36,280
Stop.

268
00:19:44,680 --> 00:19:46,590
Is this your first day?

269
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:48,650
Dump the sand over there.

270
00:19:48,830 --> 00:19:49,880
Are you blind?

271
00:19:50,740 --> 00:19:51,940
Sorry, sorry.

272
00:19:52,060 --> 00:19:52,680
Get lost.

273
00:19:56,090 --> 00:19:58,230
Young man, hurry up and work,

274
00:19:58,700 --> 00:20:00,230
or you'll lose this job too.

275
00:20:02,110 --> 00:20:02,880
Bro,

276
00:20:04,590 --> 00:20:06,240
drinking on the construction site

277
00:20:06,240 --> 00:20:07,840
is a safety hazard, isn't it?

278
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:10,860
That's our foreman, Biao.

279
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:12,410
Keep your head down here.

280
00:20:12,480 --> 00:20:14,110
We can't afford to cross him.

281
00:20:14,110 --> 00:20:15,310
Just get back to work.

282
00:20:17,970 --> 00:20:19,100
Boss.

283
00:20:21,460 --> 00:20:22,250
Hey, buddy.

284
00:20:23,730 --> 00:20:26,050
Do you buy repaired game consoles?

285
00:20:26,170 --> 00:20:26,990
Yes.

286
00:20:27,470 --> 00:20:28,620
Do you have it with you?

287
00:20:28,620 --> 00:20:30,150
Let me check the condition.

288
00:20:31,510 --> 00:20:32,570
Take a look at this.

289
00:20:37,530 --> 00:20:39,200
Did you buy this new yourself?

290
00:20:40,200 --> 00:20:41,240
Never mind that.

291
00:20:41,270 --> 00:20:42,400
How much is it worth?

292
00:20:43,880 --> 00:20:44,750
200 is the max.

293
00:20:46,110 --> 00:20:47,310
Can't you offer more?

294
00:20:47,350 --> 00:20:48,210
I really can't.

295
00:20:48,440 --> 00:20:49,600
200 is my best offer.

296
00:20:50,550 --> 00:20:51,720
Besides, buddy, this console

297
00:20:51,720 --> 00:20:52,790
has water damage, doesn't it?

298
00:20:52,790 --> 00:20:53,680
I just checked...

299
00:20:53,680 --> 00:20:55,540
The water-damaged ones are hard to sell.

300
00:20:55,540 --> 00:20:57,340
I'll check somewhere else then.

301
00:20:57,480 --> 00:20:58,590
Don't go, buddy.

302
00:20:59,070 --> 00:21:00,270
I'll add another 100.

303
00:21:00,550 --> 00:21:01,070
300.

304
00:21:06,350 --> 00:21:07,070
Bye.

305
00:21:13,800 --> 00:21:16,000
What is this stuff we eat every day?

306
00:21:16,200 --> 00:21:17,590
It's just dishwater.

307
00:21:17,590 --> 00:21:18,200
Let's get moving.

308
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:20,200
The food is getting worse and worse.

309
00:21:23,320 --> 00:21:24,440
With food like this,

310
00:21:24,440 --> 00:21:25,900
even a dog wouldn't eat it.

311
00:21:26,020 --> 00:21:27,150
Just make do with it.

312
00:21:28,240 --> 00:21:28,790
Hey, bro.

313
00:21:29,330 --> 00:21:30,990
Let's eat out when we get paid.

314
00:21:31,380 --> 00:21:33,110
We gotta actually get it first!

315
00:21:33,860 --> 00:21:34,620
Bro,

316
00:21:35,270 --> 00:21:36,000
your leg's hurt.

317
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:37,260
Maybe you should quit.

318
00:21:38,020 --> 00:21:40,880
If it doesn't heal right,
you could end up crippled.

319
00:21:41,070 --> 00:21:42,110
What else can I do?

320
00:21:42,230 --> 00:21:43,350
With my leg like this,

321
00:21:43,350 --> 00:21:45,480
what construction site would hire me?

322
00:21:45,750 --> 00:21:46,490
Besides,

323
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:48,810
they still owe me three months' wages.

324
00:21:50,330 --> 00:21:51,040
Bro.

325
00:21:52,960 --> 00:21:53,920
Where are you guys from?

326
00:21:53,920 --> 00:21:54,920
Jinfeng Village.

327
00:21:56,310 --> 00:21:58,260
Did you sign a contract?

328
00:21:58,400 --> 00:21:59,210
A contract?

329
00:21:59,550 --> 00:22:01,480
There's no such thing around here!

330
00:22:05,700 --> 00:22:06,340
[The Workers' Labor Contracts
Are All Problematic]

331
00:22:06,340 --> 00:22:07,340
[Legal Proceedings
for Unpaid Supplier Payments]

332
00:22:07,350 --> 00:22:07,440
[Illegal Employment:
Jiamei Construction Co., Ltd.]

333
00:22:07,440 --> 00:22:08,270
Bro.

334
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:08,760
Won't insurance pay
you for your injured leg?

335
00:22:08,760 --> 00:22:11,100
[Person in Charge Zhao Dabao
Accused of Being a Deadbeat Debtor]

336
00:22:11,570 --> 00:22:12,280
Come on.

337
00:22:13,270 --> 00:22:14,790
This place is shady as hell.

338
00:22:14,790 --> 00:22:17,850
They'd never bother
buying insurance for guys like us!

339
00:22:29,510 --> 00:22:31,250
I still have more of these game consoles.

340
00:22:31,250 --> 00:22:32,910
How many of these can you take?

341
00:22:33,780 --> 00:22:34,910
How many do you have?

342
00:22:35,950 --> 00:22:37,190
I've got 40.

343
00:22:40,620 --> 00:22:44,110
[Debtor: Zhao Dabao]

344
00:22:44,430 --> 00:22:45,150
[March 17, 1999]

345
00:22:45,170 --> 00:22:46,650
[Debtor: Zhao Dabao]

346
00:22:53,350 --> 00:22:54,190
[IOU]

347
00:22:54,190 --> 00:22:55,760
[Debtor: Zhao Da Bao]

348
00:22:55,780 --> 00:22:57,150
[November 24, 1998]

349
00:22:58,880 --> 00:22:59,790
White Dragon.

350
00:23:03,050 --> 00:23:03,920
White Dragon.

351
00:23:04,350 --> 00:23:05,030
One Dot.

352
00:23:05,050 --> 00:23:06,050
Who is Zhao Dabao?

353
00:23:08,270 --> 00:23:09,110
You punk.

354
00:23:09,320 --> 00:23:10,920
How dare you call Mr. Zhao
by his given name!

355
00:23:10,920 --> 00:23:11,590
Red Dragon.

356
00:23:16,110 --> 00:23:16,920
Green Dragon.

357
00:23:17,510 --> 00:23:18,970
I'm here to collect a debt.

358
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:20,350
Here is the IOU.

359
00:23:23,960 --> 00:23:24,930
Six Bamboos.

360
00:23:25,590 --> 00:23:26,650
Three Characters.

361
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:30,000
Four Characters.

362
00:23:35,710 --> 00:23:38,200
The workers' labor contracts
are all problematic.

363
00:23:38,200 --> 00:23:41,730
You'll have to pay huge compensation
if they go to arbitration.

364
00:23:42,700 --> 00:23:45,180
And regarding the balance
you owe suppliers,

365
00:23:45,180 --> 00:23:46,580
if legal action is taken,

366
00:23:47,020 --> 00:23:49,440
you'll have to pay no less than
triple the penalty damages.

367
00:23:49,440 --> 00:23:50,550
Also, the municipal projects

368
00:23:50,550 --> 00:23:51,810
your company is involved in...

369
00:23:51,810 --> 00:23:54,410
The materials used
don't comply with the tender requirements.

370
00:23:54,410 --> 00:23:56,070
The rebar doesn't meet national standards.

371
00:23:56,070 --> 00:23:57,670
The cement grade is unclear.

372
00:23:58,440 --> 00:23:59,970
If you add all that money up,

373
00:24:00,190 --> 00:24:02,850
it's far more than the amount
stated on this IOU.

374
00:24:05,430 --> 00:24:06,300
Bro,

375
00:24:07,130 --> 00:24:09,100
do you even know

376
00:24:09,750 --> 00:24:11,750
who's backing this project of ours?

377
00:24:11,840 --> 00:24:12,950
I don't know.

378
00:24:13,600 --> 00:24:15,330
And it has nothing to do with me.

379
00:24:15,720 --> 00:24:17,250
I just want the money today.

380
00:24:18,310 --> 00:24:20,370
Or, your site will be shut down today.

381
00:24:21,320 --> 00:24:23,350
What the hell are you?

382
00:24:37,440 --> 00:24:38,510
Pay up.

383
00:24:42,440 --> 00:24:43,030
Beat him.

384
00:24:43,270 --> 00:24:44,340
Beat him to death.

385
00:24:50,880 --> 00:24:51,740
That's enough.

386
00:25:11,760 --> 00:25:12,800
Pay up.

387
00:25:15,920 --> 00:25:17,750
Pay back shit!

388
00:25:17,790 --> 00:25:20,040
Not a fucking cent!

389
00:25:24,180 --> 00:25:26,340
If you can get this million back,

390
00:25:26,360 --> 00:25:27,470
I promise you,

391
00:25:27,500 --> 00:25:29,430
no one will bother your parents

392
00:25:29,450 --> 00:25:30,560
or friends.

393
00:25:30,590 --> 00:25:31,640
What do you think?

394
00:25:33,320 --> 00:25:35,300
Is this idiot out of his mind?

395
00:25:35,350 --> 00:25:36,680
How dare he threaten us!

396
00:25:54,110 --> 00:25:55,770
What are you looking at me for?

397
00:25:57,240 --> 00:25:58,270
You want to hit me?

398
00:25:58,400 --> 00:25:59,230
Come on!

399
00:26:06,590 --> 00:26:07,830
Don't move, anyone!

400
00:26:10,110 --> 00:26:11,680
Whoever moves dies!

401
00:26:13,590 --> 00:26:15,250
Are you going to pay off or not?

402
00:26:16,830 --> 00:26:18,400
Bring the money!

403
00:26:28,690 --> 00:26:32,770
[Harmony Is Paramount]

404
00:26:47,700 --> 00:26:49,030
Go wash your face first.

405
00:26:50,370 --> 00:26:51,090
No need.

406
00:27:01,860 --> 00:27:05,140
[Harmony Is Paramount]

407
00:27:05,550 --> 00:27:07,430
It's the 8% commission I promised you.

408
00:27:07,430 --> 00:27:08,230
[Harmony Is Paramount]

409
00:27:08,230 --> 00:27:09,030
Take it.

410
00:27:12,030 --> 00:27:13,230
I still owe you money,

411
00:27:13,870 --> 00:27:14,990
so I'll pay you back with this first.

412
00:27:14,990 --> 00:27:16,250
Business is business.

413
00:27:27,590 --> 00:27:28,400
Uncle San,

414
00:27:29,260 --> 00:27:31,120
I'd like to beg you to do me a favor.

415
00:27:32,750 --> 00:27:34,470
Can you help me find this girl?

416
00:27:44,100 --> 00:27:45,050
Ming,

417
00:27:46,510 --> 00:27:47,680
when you asked to borrow money before,

418
00:27:47,680 --> 00:27:49,200
I didn't ask what you wanted to do.

419
00:27:49,200 --> 00:27:51,910
Whatever you did
had nothing to do with me anyway.

420
00:27:51,910 --> 00:27:53,260
But now you work for me,

421
00:27:53,750 --> 00:27:55,750
so I have to remind you of something.

422
00:27:57,110 --> 00:27:59,170
Don't end up landing yourself in jail

423
00:28:00,070 --> 00:28:01,510
over a woman!

424
00:28:34,110 --> 00:28:34,640
Ah!

425
00:28:34,700 --> 00:28:36,680
Help! Quick! Someone help me!

426
00:28:36,680 --> 00:28:38,110
Someone help! Help!

427
00:28:52,200 --> 00:28:53,110
You're awake.

428
00:28:58,070 --> 00:28:59,020
Take it easy.

429
00:29:05,040 --> 00:29:07,040
Don't worry, the baby is fine.

430
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:09,720
It's a good thing you came in time.

431
00:29:09,720 --> 00:29:12,050
Otherwise, you would have been in danger.

432
00:29:13,200 --> 00:29:14,400
Where is your family?

433
00:29:14,550 --> 00:29:16,210
Why aren't they here with you?

434
00:29:19,640 --> 00:29:21,480
Stay for a few days for observation.

435
00:29:21,480 --> 00:29:23,810
You can be discharged once you're better.

436
00:29:24,200 --> 00:29:25,110
Doctor.

437
00:29:25,400 --> 00:29:26,070
Yes?

438
00:29:29,200 --> 00:29:30,590
How much will this cost?

439
00:29:31,070 --> 00:29:32,470
Let me ask the nurse for you.

440
00:29:32,470 --> 00:29:33,270
Wang,

441
00:29:33,640 --> 00:29:35,720
check the medical expenses for Bed Six.

442
00:29:35,720 --> 00:29:36,960
Wait a moment, let me calculate.

443
00:29:36,960 --> 00:29:37,350
Okay.

444
00:29:39,720 --> 00:29:41,350
It's okay. Don't worry.

445
00:29:41,720 --> 00:29:42,580
Just rest well.

446
00:29:44,720 --> 00:29:46,850
Including the emergency ambulance fee,

447
00:29:46,850 --> 00:29:48,700
the total is 3,227 yuan.

448
00:29:53,030 --> 00:29:54,760
Do you have medical insurance?

449
00:29:56,000 --> 00:29:57,880
You need to go to the payment office
on the first floor

450
00:29:57,880 --> 00:29:59,110
to pay the deposit.

451
00:30:00,790 --> 00:30:02,200
Don't think too much about it for now.

452
00:30:02,200 --> 00:30:03,660
Just focus on recovering.

453
00:30:43,070 --> 00:30:45,640
Hello, can I help you?

454
00:30:46,440 --> 00:30:47,640
Move everything out!

455
00:30:48,070 --> 00:30:49,000
No, no...

456
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:50,400
Wait, what are you guys doing?

457
00:30:50,400 --> 00:30:51,960
Who did you sell these goods to?

458
00:30:51,960 --> 00:30:53,830
We've been keeping an eye on you
for a long time.

459
00:30:53,830 --> 00:30:55,490
Where did you get these goods?

460
00:30:56,550 --> 00:30:57,880
I found them.

461
00:30:58,790 --> 00:30:59,880
You did?

462
00:31:01,570 --> 00:31:03,330
Do you even know I'm the only one

463
00:31:03,480 --> 00:31:05,740
selling these game consoles in Nanping?

464
00:31:05,830 --> 00:31:07,430
Even I struggle to get stock,

465
00:31:07,790 --> 00:31:08,990
but you 'found them'?

466
00:31:10,120 --> 00:31:11,400
No, really, I found them.

467
00:31:11,400 --> 00:31:12,860
I found them off the coast.

468
00:31:19,480 --> 00:31:21,410
Boss, some of the stock is missing.

469
00:31:26,240 --> 00:31:27,370
Where are the goods?

470
00:31:31,590 --> 00:31:33,450
These consoles got waterlogged.

471
00:31:34,550 --> 00:31:36,680
I repaired them and sold them.

472
00:31:38,110 --> 00:31:39,350
You repaired them?

473
00:31:40,110 --> 00:31:42,170
You know how to repair game consoles?

474
00:31:43,680 --> 00:31:44,400
Yes.

475
00:31:58,120 --> 00:31:59,580
Take the money for now.

476
00:31:59,600 --> 00:32:01,600
You'll repair our stock from now on.

477
00:32:05,030 --> 00:32:05,800
Do well.

478
00:32:06,100 --> 00:32:06,620
See you.

479
00:32:25,890 --> 00:32:28,180
[Outstanding Debt: 190,000 Yuan]

480
00:32:28,200 --> 00:32:35,480
[Outstanding Debt: 182,000 Yuan]

481
00:32:52,750 --> 00:32:53,270
What?

482
00:32:53,950 --> 00:32:54,800
Take it.

483
00:32:56,830 --> 00:32:58,040
We went there together,

484
00:32:58,040 --> 00:32:59,770
so let's split it fifty-fifty.

485
00:33:01,660 --> 00:33:02,640
You're crazy.

486
00:33:03,550 --> 00:33:05,790
You deserve this.  Keep it safe.

487
00:33:09,520 --> 00:33:11,160
I never expected
a college student like you

488
00:33:11,160 --> 00:33:12,620
to be such a tough fighter!

489
00:33:12,640 --> 00:33:15,440
Stick with me from now on.

490
00:33:15,440 --> 00:33:16,400
You got that?

491
00:33:19,920 --> 00:33:22,860
Do you have to be so loyal, Ming?

492
00:33:33,640 --> 00:33:35,030
Where are you taking me?

493
00:33:35,110 --> 00:33:36,780
Didn't I tell you?

494
00:33:37,110 --> 00:33:40,430
Uncle San prepared
a so-called river-view villa for you.

495
00:33:40,590 --> 00:33:42,050
I bet you'll be satisfied.

496
00:33:48,090 --> 00:33:49,280
This is it.

497
00:33:54,770 --> 00:33:56,770
The grand river-view villa.

498
00:33:59,460 --> 00:34:01,570
It's warm in winter and cool in summer,

499
00:34:01,570 --> 00:34:03,340
with a wide view.

500
00:34:04,310 --> 00:34:06,630
It'll cheer you up a bit.

501
00:34:09,190 --> 00:34:10,389
Over here! Come on in!

502
00:34:14,810 --> 00:34:15,770
How is it?

503
00:34:16,110 --> 00:34:16,770
Satisfied?

504
00:34:18,280 --> 00:34:19,139
Well then, I...

505
00:34:24,710 --> 00:34:27,510
Two buddies working together
make the job easier!

506
00:34:33,429 --> 00:34:34,889
This river-view house...

507
00:34:35,360 --> 00:34:37,590
Uncle San really cares about you, huh?

508
00:34:47,920 --> 00:34:49,880
It's not bad once it's tidied up.

509
00:34:58,150 --> 00:35:00,550
Speak up
if you have something on your mind,

510
00:35:00,550 --> 00:35:02,520
and we'll sort things out together.

511
00:35:02,520 --> 00:35:03,320
Don't worry.

512
00:35:04,110 --> 00:35:05,110
I'm fine.

513
00:35:07,830 --> 00:35:11,190
[Kesheng Technology Company]

514
00:35:11,220 --> 00:35:15,060
[Are you back?]

515
00:35:16,100 --> 00:35:18,060
Who's paging you this late?

516
00:35:22,130 --> 00:35:23,590
Haven't you found her yet?

517
00:35:23,810 --> 00:35:25,100
No news yet.

518
00:35:25,590 --> 00:35:27,440
What have those two been up to lately?

519
00:35:27,440 --> 00:35:29,880
After being laid off,
Lin Hua got a job as a lighthouse keeper.

520
00:35:29,880 --> 00:35:31,510
After Lu Ming returned to Nanping,

521
00:35:31,510 --> 00:35:34,110
he got a job collecting debts
for Sancheng Financial Firm.

522
00:35:34,110 --> 00:35:36,770
Neither of them
seems to have contacted Xia Xue.

523
00:35:37,130 --> 00:35:38,780
Lu Ming went to Lao San's?

524
00:35:38,920 --> 00:35:40,670
Yes. The money he gave Li Dong

525
00:35:40,710 --> 00:35:42,310
was borrowed from him.

526
00:35:42,340 --> 00:35:44,400
His family was also harassed by them.

527
00:35:44,400 --> 00:35:45,710
He must have had no choice

528
00:35:45,710 --> 00:35:47,110
but to take the job there.

529
00:35:56,110 --> 00:35:57,910
They're both college students,

530
00:35:59,480 --> 00:36:01,140
so they don't have much money.

531
00:36:14,150 --> 00:36:15,020
Hou,

532
00:36:15,550 --> 00:36:17,810
contact Li from the Finance Department.

533
00:36:18,230 --> 00:36:19,760
Have him come to the bank with me

534
00:36:19,760 --> 00:36:21,690
to handle some personal business.

535
00:36:55,690 --> 00:36:57,220
What happened to your face?

536
00:36:59,550 --> 00:37:01,680
Got into a little misunderstanding
with someone.

537
00:37:01,680 --> 00:37:03,610
You don't look any better than I do.

538
00:37:04,000 --> 00:37:04,920
What happened?

539
00:37:06,790 --> 00:37:08,850
I bumped into something by accident.

540
00:37:14,510 --> 00:37:15,770
Any news about Xia Xue?

541
00:37:18,230 --> 00:37:19,430
Still asking around.

542
00:37:29,150 --> 00:37:31,480
What're you gonna do now that you're back?

543
00:37:35,070 --> 00:37:36,530
I'm working for Uncle San.

544
00:37:38,550 --> 00:37:39,440
Why?

545
00:37:42,630 --> 00:37:43,880
Don't worry about me.

546
00:37:44,710 --> 00:37:46,590
I heard the shipyard had layoffs.

547
00:37:47,070 --> 00:37:48,930
They didn't lay you off, did they?

548
00:37:50,210 --> 00:37:51,540
Hundreds were laid off,

549
00:37:52,840 --> 00:37:54,230
but I left on my own.

550
00:37:56,070 --> 00:37:58,130
What kind of work have you been doing?

551
00:38:01,590 --> 00:38:03,250
I'm guarding the lighthouse.

552
00:38:06,130 --> 00:38:08,130
Why would you go guard a lighthouse?

553
00:38:08,550 --> 00:38:10,490
Why can't I?

554
00:38:10,880 --> 00:38:12,060
It's free food and housing.

555
00:38:12,060 --> 00:38:14,920
And I don't have to watch Old Lin
throw a drunken fit.

556
00:38:18,440 --> 00:38:19,800
What's with that look?

557
00:38:21,880 --> 00:38:23,000
I'm fine.

558
00:38:24,960 --> 00:38:26,400
I'm doing fine living alone.

559
00:38:26,400 --> 00:38:28,230
No need to deal with the outside world.

560
00:38:28,230 --> 00:38:29,090
It's peaceful.

561
00:38:37,170 --> 00:38:37,940
Lin Hua.

562
00:38:39,800 --> 00:38:42,330
You're not hiding something from me,
are you?

563
00:38:48,280 --> 00:38:49,620
You know me so well.

564
00:38:51,480 --> 00:38:54,320
Fine, I won't hide it.

565
00:38:57,560 --> 00:38:59,020
I saved some money for you.

566
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:00,840
I...

567
00:39:01,310 --> 00:39:02,840
found a way to make money.

568
00:39:03,380 --> 00:39:05,490
It's not much, but just take it for now.

569
00:39:05,490 --> 00:39:06,690
I'll earn more later.

570
00:39:09,230 --> 00:39:10,160
What kind of way?

571
00:39:12,440 --> 00:39:13,900
Repairing game consoles.

572
00:39:14,320 --> 00:39:15,510
Water-damaged

573
00:39:15,510 --> 00:39:16,640
and defective ones.

574
00:39:16,960 --> 00:39:18,820
I can earn a lot by repairing them.

575
00:39:23,030 --> 00:39:24,890
My trouble is already sorted out.

576
00:39:25,280 --> 00:39:27,840
Give this money to your mom.

577
00:39:36,710 --> 00:39:37,550
Lu Ming.

578
00:39:38,980 --> 00:39:40,600
If this is about money,

579
00:39:41,030 --> 00:39:42,690
we can figure it out together.

580
00:39:43,630 --> 00:39:46,030
But collecting for loan sharks
is too dangerous.

581
00:39:46,030 --> 00:39:46,960
If Xia Xue knows,

582
00:39:46,960 --> 00:39:48,290
she won't agree either.

583
00:39:54,950 --> 00:39:56,410
I'm working with Uncle San

584
00:39:57,190 --> 00:39:58,480
not just for the debt.

585
00:39:59,140 --> 00:40:00,110
Then why?

586
00:40:02,930 --> 00:40:05,590
He has a great influence
on both sides of the law.

587
00:40:06,360 --> 00:40:09,020
Working with him
makes it easier to find Xia Xue.

588
00:40:11,210 --> 00:40:12,040
Also,

589
00:40:13,360 --> 00:40:16,230
I heard Uncle San has a grudge
against Ma Derong.

590
00:40:18,110 --> 00:40:19,570
I need to use his influence

591
00:40:20,280 --> 00:40:21,370
to take down Ma Derong.

592
00:40:21,370 --> 00:40:22,490
Think carefully.

593
00:40:23,510 --> 00:40:25,110
Once you step into this mess,

594
00:40:25,210 --> 00:40:26,500
there's no going back.

595
00:40:39,920 --> 00:40:41,480
As long as we can be free,

596
00:40:44,010 --> 00:40:45,680
I don't care what I become.
